                            <comment id="15172867" author="wzheng" created="Mon, 29 Feb 2016 23:31:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Operations related to table creation will normally lowercase the db/table names before doing certain tasks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But for ALTER TABLE things are different. Specifically, if a table is renamed and given a new mixed-case name, HDFS directory is created with mixed case as is. That is not consistent to CREATE TABLE behavior. Moreover, this will cause issue for example if users want to load data directly to HDFS under the table directory, or use some scripts to check data size on HDFS path.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example&lt;/p&gt;
